Jai Courtney (born ) is an Australian actor known for his role as Varro in "", and for his roles in the feature films "Jack Reacher" and "A Good Day to Die Hard".
Personal life.
Jai Courtney was born and raised in Sydney, Australia. His father, Chris, worked for a state-owned electricity company, and his mother, Karen, was a teacher at the primary school, Galston Public School, that Courtney attended.
Career.
In 2008, Courtney had a lead role in the hit Australian series "Packed to the Rafters" and a guest lead in the popular "All Saints". He was in the comedy feature "To Hell & Bourke" and several short films. Courtney's big break came in 2010 when he played Varro in "". Courtney played Charlie in "Jack Reacher", which starred Tom Cruise, and John McClane's son, Jack, in "A Good Day to Die Hard".
